.TH "WALLPAPER-PICKER" "1" "2026-04-09" "1.0.0" "Wallpaper Picker Manual"
.nh
.ad l

.SH NAME
wallpaper\-picker \- A sleek, feature\-rich video wallpaper manager for Arch Linux/Hyprland

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wallpaper\-picker
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wallpaper\-picker
is a powerful command\-line tool for managing video wallpapers on Hyprland and other wlroots\-based Wayland compositors. It provides an interactive TUI picker, slideshow mode, multi\-monitor support, and deep integration with Arch Linux.

.PP
Features include:
.RS
\(bu Interactive fzf\-based picker with video preview
\(bu Random, slideshow, and sequential playback modes
\(bu Multi\-monitor support with auto\-detection
\(bu Thumbnail caching for faster browsing
\(bu Favorites and history tracking
\(bu Systemd user service for auto\-start
\(bu Shell completions for bash, zsh, and fish
.RE

.SH COMMANDS

.SS Core Commands
.TP
.B pick
Open the interactive wallpaper picker with fzf. Displays a searchable list of all wallpapers with optional video preview.
.TP
.B browse
Browse and select any video file from your system. Useful for one\-off wallpapers not in your collection.
.TP
.B random
Set a random wallpaper from your collection.
.TP
.B slideshow [\fISECONDS\fR]
Start slideshow mode, cycling through all wallpapers. Default interval is 30 seconds unless specified.
.TP
.B stop
Stop the current wallpaper playback.
.TP
.B current
Display information about the currently active wallpaper.
.TP
.B next / prev
Switch to the next or previous wallpaper in the collection.

.SS Management Commands
.TP
.B list
List all available wallpapers with their status.
.TP
.B add\-dir \fIPATH\fR
Add a directory to watch for wallpapers. Directories are stored in \fI~/.config/wallpaper\-picker/watch\-dirs\fR.
.TP
.B remove\-dir \fIPATH\fR
Remove a directory from the watch list.
.TP
.B watch\-dirs
List all directories being watched for wallpapers.
.TP
.B toggle\-fav [\fIFILE\fR]
Toggle the favorite status of a wallpaper. If no file specified, uses current wallpaper.
.TP
.B config
Open the configuration file in your default editor (\fI$EDITOR\fR).

.SS System Commands
.TP
.B monitors
List all available monitors and show which one is active.
.TP
.B clear\-cache
Clear the thumbnail cache at \fI~/.cache/wallpaper\-picker/thumbnails/\fR.
.TP
.B status
Show detailed system status including configuration, statistics, and running state.
.TP
.B doctor
Run dependency checks and diagnose common issues.
.TP
.B enable\-startup
Enable the systemd user service to start slideshow on login.
.TP
.B disable\-startup
Disable the systemd user service.

.SS Help Commands
.TP
.B help
Display this help message.
.TP
.B --version, -v
Show version information.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-m, \-\-monitor \fINAME\fR
Specify which monitor to use. Use \fBmonitors\fR command to see available options.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-dir \fIPATH\fR
Override the default wallpaper directory.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-no\-notify
Disable desktop notifications.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored at \fI~/.config/wallpaper\-picker/config\fR and uses shell variable syntax:

.PP
.nf
.RS
# Monitor configuration
MONITOR=""
AUTO_DETECT_MONITOR="yes"

# Directory configuration
DEFAULT_WALLPAPER_DIR="$HOME/Videos/wallpapers"

# Playback configuration
ENABLE_AUDIO="no"
LOOP_MODE="inf"

# Slideshow configuration
SLIDESHOW_INTERVAL=30
SLIDESHOW_SHUFFLE="no"

# UI configuration
THUMBNAIL_ENABLED="yes"
CACHE_THUMBNAILS="yes"
NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED="yes"

# Startup configuration
STARTUP_MODE="manual"
.RE
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/wallpaper\-picker/config
Main configuration file.
.TP
.B ~/.config/wallpaper\-picker/watch\-dirs
List of additional directories to watch.
.TP
.B ~/.cache/wallpaper\-picker/state.json
Current wallpaper state.
.TP
.B ~/.cache/wallpaper\-picker/thumbnails/
Cached video thumbnails.
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/wallpaper\-picker/history
Wallpaper usage history.
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/wallpaper\-picker/favorites
List of favorited wallpapers.

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS Interactive Selection
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ wallpaper\-picker pick
.RE

.SS Random Wallpaper
.PP
.nf
.R
$ wallpaper\-picker random
.RE

.SS Slideshow with Custom Interval
.PP
.nf
.R
$ wallpaper\-picker slideshow 60
.RE

.SS Specific Monitor
.PP
.nf
.R
$ wallpaper\-picker -m HDMI-A-1 pick
.RE

.SS Add New Wallpaper Directory
.PP
.nf
.R
$ wallpaper\-picker add-dir ~/Downloads/wallpapers
.RE

.SS Check System Status
.PP
.nf
.R
$ wallpaper\-picker doctor
.RE

.SH HYPERLAND INTEGRATION
Add these bindings to \fI~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf\fR:

.PP
.nf
.RS
# Interactive picker
bind = SUPER, W, exec, wallpaper\-picker pick

# Browse files
bind = SUPER SHIFT, W, exec, wallpaper\-picker browse

# Random wallpaper
bind = SUPER CTRL, W, exec, wallpaper\-picker random

# Stop wallpaper
bind = SUPER ALT, W, exec, wallpaper\-picker stop
.RE

.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required
.BR mpvpaper (AUR)
Video wallpaper utility for wlroots
.br
.BR fzf
Fuzzy finder for interactive picker
.br
.BR mpv
Media player for previews
.br
.BR jq
JSON processing for state management

.TP
.B Optional
.BR ffmpeg
Video thumbnails and metadata
.br
.BR libnotify
Desktop notifications
.br
.BR systemd
Startup service support

.SH INSTALLATION

.SS From AUR
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ yay -S wallpaper\-picker
.RE

.SS Manual Installation
.PP
.nf
.R
$ curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/shadowarch/wallpaper-picker/main/wallpaper-picker -o ~/.local/bin/wallpaper-picker
$ chmod +x ~/.local/bin/wallpaper-picker
.RE

